      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;SaragothM wrote:&lt;br&gt;Don't get me wrong, I think this server would have been a great idea 4 years ago.. Why now though? When so much of the community just wants a plain old classic server or why not both?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Because you'll get a progression server, but not a classic one.  A classic server will take too much time to set up, because of the massive changes to the game that would need to be made in order to revert back to the classic rules.  Plus, after a short time, the classic server people would become bored, and want to have other expansions opened up to them. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If this is wildly successful, then perhaps the investment in a classic server may be considered (note the qualifiers, wildly successful and perhaps.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
